| `PORT_RANGES` | `packages/shared/src/constants/deployment.ts` | `PREVIEW_MIN: 4000`, `PREVIEW_MAX: 4999` |
| `HEALTH_CHECK` | `packages/shared/src/constants/deployment.ts` | `MAX_RETRIES: 10`, `RETRY_INTERVAL_MS: 2000` |

---

## Design Decision: New Class vs. Extended Deployer

Two approaches are available:

**Option A: New `PreviewDeployer` class** (recommended for Phase 7)
- Separate file at `packages/core/src/deploy/preview-deployer.ts`
- Contains preview-specific logic (PR-based image tagging, preview URL generation, preview env vars)
- Can reuse `PortAllocator` and `CaddyClient` by composition
- Easier to understand and modify independently

**Option B: Extend `Deployer` with a `type` parameter**
- Single class handles both production and preview
- Risk of coupling production and preview logic

Option A is recommended because preview deployments have distinct behavior around image tagging, old container cleanup (per-PR, not per-project), and URL generation.

