## Verification Checklist

- [ ] `PreviewDeployer` class created at `packages/core/src/deploy/preview-deployer.ts`
- [ ] Image tagged as `{slug}:pr-{N}-{sha7}` (7 char short SHA)
- [ ] Port allocated from 4000-4999 range using `PortAllocator`
- [ ] Container started with preview-scope env vars
- [ ] Health check retries up to 10 times with 2s interval
- [ ] Caddy route added: `pr-{N}--{slug}.{domain}` -> `localhost:{port}`
- [ ] Deployment record updated to `ready` with `url`, `port`, `containerId`, `dockerImageTag`, `buildDurationMs`
- [ ] Previous preview container for same PR is stopped and archived
- [ ] Build failure sets deployment to `failed` with `errorMessage`
- [ ] Health check failure stops container and releases port
- [ ] Port allocation failure results in clean failure
- [ ] Temporary env file deleted after container starts
- [ ] Container labeled with gblockparty metadata (type, project, PR, deployment)

---

## Output

After this step:
- Preview containers can be built and started for any PR
- Each preview is accessible at a unique port in the 4000-4999 range
- Caddy routes traffic from `pr-{N}--{slug}.domain` to the container
- Deployment records track the full state of each preview
- Failed deployments are cleaned up with resources released
